title: Bug 110566: Incorrect data set result returned when an invalid filter expression 'row[0]' is set
description: When a filter 'row[0] equals to 0' is set, the data set returns an incorrect result. It either returns null result set or provides incorrect data.
OB: The data set returns an incorrect result or a null result set when the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0' is set.
EB: The data set should return the correct result based on the filter expression 'row[0] equals to 0'.
SR:
To reproduce the bug:
1. Set the filter expression as 'row[0] equals to 0'
2. Execute the data set query
3. Observe the incorrect result or a null result set returned
